ivardefs.name: accept
ivardefs.desc: The mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Accept' header.

ivardefs.name: contentType
ivardefs.desc: The mime-type to use for RESTful operation in the 'Content-Type' header.

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: The description would be used by test engines for tracking and reporting purposes.

ivardefs.name: destination
ivardefs.desc: The server where the request message is destined for.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.destination section.

ivardefs.name: encodeRequestUrl
ivardefs.desc: Whether or not to implicitly send the request url in encoded format. The default is true to match the standard RESTful client behavior. Set to false when communicating with a server that does not support encoded url paths.

ivardefs.name: label
ivardefs.desc: The label would be used for tracking/logging purposes by test engines.

ivardefs.name: method
ivardefs.desc: The HTTP method the test engine MUST use for this operation regardless of any other operation details.

ivardefs.name: origin
ivardefs.desc: The server where the request message originates from.  Must be one of the server numbers listed in TestScript.origin section.

ivardefs.name: params
ivardefs.desc: Path plus parameters after [type].  Used to set parts of the request URL explicitly.

ivardefs.name: requestHeader_
ivardefs.desc: Header elements would be used to set HTTP headers.

ivardefs.name: requestId
ivardefs.desc: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the request.

ivardefs.name: resource
ivardefs.desc: The type of the resource.  See http://build.fhir.org/resourcelist.html.

ivardefs.name: responseId
ivardefs.desc: The fixture id (maybe new) to map to the response.

ivardefs.name: sourceId
ivardefs.desc: The id of the fixture used as the body of a PUT or POST request.

ivardefs.name: targetId
ivardefs.desc: Id of fixture used for extracting the [id],  [type], and [vid] for GET requests.
